---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-cream">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12" data-reveal>
      <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">Real Engagements</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-primary leading-tight">
        What this looks like in practice
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6" data-reveal-stagger>
      <!-- Case Study 1: Board Prep -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-7">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-secondary/10 text-secondary text-[10px] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Board Governance</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Pre-IPO Biopharma</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-primary mb-3">Built the entire board prep process from zero</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A clinical-stage biotech was 6 weeks from their first board meeting with new investors. No prep process, no materials template, no action tracking. The CEO was assembling everything himself the night before.
        </p>
        <div class="border-t border-primary/[0.06] pt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-1">What I built:</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Complete board prep lifecycle: T-minus 3 week materials timeline, template deck, committee briefing docs, individual pre-meeting packages for each board member, real-time minutes, and post-meeting action tracker with owners and deadlines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-secondary/5 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-semibold">Board materials delivered 5 business days early, every quarter. After a last-minute date change, delivered the complete package 4 hours ahead of a 48-hour deadline. System still in use 18+ months later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Case Study 2: Investor Relations -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-7">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-secondary/10 text-secondary text-[10px] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Investor Relations</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Publicly Traded Cannabis, $562M Revenue</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-primary mb-3">200+ stakeholders across 7 markets. Nothing fell through.</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A publicly traded multi-state operator with $562M in annual revenue had no centralized investor communications system. Stakeholders were pinging the CEO directly. Quarterly updates went out late. Nobody owned the relationship layer.
        </p>
        <div class="border-t border-primary/[0.06] pt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-1">What I built:</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Full IR tracking system with stakeholder categorization, standardized correspondence templates for quarterly updates and ad-hoc requests, and a reporting workflow that kept 200+ investors, board members, and scientific advisors in the loop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-secondary/5 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-semibold">Cut investor response time from 3-5 business days to 24 hours. 98% stakeholder satisfaction. CEO freed up 15+ hours per month.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Case Study 3: Executive Onboarding -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-7">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-secondary/10 text-secondary text-[10px] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Executive Onboarding</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Financial Services</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-primary mb-3">New executives went from 90 days to hit stride to under 60</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          New leaders were spending their first month figuring out who to talk to, what meetings mattered, and how things actually worked. Knowledge lived in people's heads. Every leadership transition started from scratch.
        </p>
        <div class="border-t border-primary/[0.06] pt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-1">What I built:</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">90-day onboarding playbook: stakeholder map with relationship context, meeting cadence guide, decision-rights matrix showing who owns what, and communication rhythm documentation so new leaders knew exactly how the organization worked from day one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-secondary/5 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-semibold">20% faster executive ramp-up. New leaders productive from week one instead of month three.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Case Study 4: Multi-State Coordination -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-7">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-secondary/10 text-secondary text-[10px] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Multi-State Ops</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Cannabis, 46 Locations</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-primary mb-3">46 locations across 7 states. Coordination went from chaos to clockwork.</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Cross-functional meetings took 5 days to schedule. Nothing was standardized across state lines. Compliance gaps kept emerging because nobody owned the operational connective tissue between markets.
        </p>
        <div class="border-t border-primary/[0.06] pt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-1">What I built:</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Centralized multi-state scheduling system, shared operations calendar, standardized cross-location communication protocols, and compliance tracking templates for each market.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-secondary/5 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-semibold">Reduced scheduling conflicts by 60%. Cut cross-state meeting coordination from 5 days to 2.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Case Study 5: AI Workflow Integration -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-7">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-secondary/10 text-secondary text-[10px] font-bold tracking-wider uppercase px-3 py-1 rounded-full">AI Integration</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Cross-Industry</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg text-primary mb-3">AI-augmented operations before most EAs knew what a prompt was</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Started using Claude AI and Perplexity for executive operations work in 2024, well before most administrative professionals considered AI part of the toolkit. Applied it to the work that actually eats time: drafting correspondence, stakeholder research, meeting prep, and report assembly.
        </p>
        <div class="border-t border-primary/[0.06] pt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-1">What changed:</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Built repeatable AI workflows for investor correspondence drafting, board materials research, and executive briefing preparation. Not replacing judgment with automation, but eliminating the busywork so more time goes to strategic thinking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-secondary/5 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-semibold">40% faster draft preparation. Time reclaimed goes directly into higher-value strategic work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
